<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Once Upon A Time:</strong> Storybrooke is SCP-3088, and Greg Mendell is a Foundation agent sent to investigate, along with the personal goal of finding his missing father.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
<strong>The Twilight Zone:</strong> Rod Serling is either A) A reality bender that gets bored B) A researcher (or O5) reminding us of uncontained SCP's, or C) A Serpent's Hand member that is continuously leaking SCP's
<p><strong>Doctor Who:</strong> The Doctor may be a Thaumiel SCP from another Foundation's universe sent to, not contain, but <em>resolve</em> anomalies in their respective realities. Bonus, maybe he wasn't even enlisted by the Foundation. Bonus Bonus, the TARDIS is really an interdimensional portal machine.</p>
<p><strong>Manifest:</strong> The Foundation may be behind-the-scenes investigating the anomaly, and the initial landing and questionings may have been performed by Foundation agents.</p>

