														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4083323">
									

<p>Warehouse 13 is another obvious one.</p>
<p>The Lost Room mini-series had the right subject matter and tone. Doesn't have any real parallel organization for the Foundation itself, but certain characters would fit in well with various GoIs. And the show establishes its own clear &quot;SCP-001&quot; mythos.</p>
<p>Preacher could be set in the SCP-verse; with Jesse and pals only encountering a bare handful of the anomalies out there. Features 343 in a particularly co-dependent phase. He doesn't like to talk about it.</p>
<p>American Gods could be about an extended family of uncontained humanoid skips. Or about a single keter, reality-bending, memetic(?) anomaly that makes sufficiently accumulated belief manifest as humanoids.</p>

							</div>

								
					
